name: initNonEmpty
description:
Get all but the last element of a non empty array, creating a new array.
*Example
documentation:
Get all but the last element of a non empty array, creating a new array.
*Example**

```ts
import { Array } from "effect"

const result = Array.initNonEmpty([1, 2, 3, 4])
console.log(result) // [1, 2, 3]
```
